						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in a lane near the Hoṇḍa.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record states that the hero-stone was set up by <hi rend="bold">Maleya-Nāyaka</hi> in memory of a hero, probably the servant of <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> <hi rend="bold">Mādarasa.</hi> The characters are of about the <hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi> Mādarasa is stated to be a devotee of <hi rend="bold">Dhavaḷanātha of Kālaḍi</hi> (cf. B.K. No. 70 of 1932-33).</p>						

						</summary>
